    "introduction": "Kelly Collins Lintz has been a working actress for over 30 years, appearing in films like We're the Millers, Gifted, Boys of Summer and Miracles From Heaven, and on network series like Surface, Army Wives, and One Tree Hill.When her four children (Mackenzie, Matt, Madison and Macsen) followed her into the industry, they bravely navigated the shark infested waters of Hollywood together, spending time on shows like The Walking Dead, the Alienist, Under the Dome, Bosch, and Ms. Marvel. The fact that they became series regulars long before she did, does not make her bitter at all...Now that her children have left her alone once more, she is free to pursue a new goal of creating family and inspirational content that will hopefully keep them all employed until the end of time. Or at least long enough to earn their health benefits.She is in development for her first screenplay, Able, the story of Amy Kosmalski, a mother who gives birth to a little girl with Down Syndrome, and moves mountains to ensure her daughter lives a life of full inclusion.",
